  <!--
    🚫 Arcade / MAME — openemu.system.arcade
    The Arcade system plugin (UI layer) exists at OpenEmu/SystemPlugins/Arcade/ and is fully
    configured with controller mappings, file types (.zip, .7z, .chd, .bin, .rom), and 8-player
    support. However, there is NO MAME emulation core in this project.

    This is why users see a greyed-out Arcade entry in Settings → Cores with nothing to select.

    A MAME core would need to:
      - Subclass OEGameCore and implement OEArcadeSystemResponderClient
      - Compile MAME (modern versions support ARM64/AArch64 natively)
      - Register here under openemu.system.arcade

    Tracking issue: https://github.com/nickybmon/openemu-silicon/issues/25
  -->


